records.addlTxt:
Proposed Order of Commitment for Treatment  Form CR 206
(sent to Br 2 for signing)

Attorney Emily Gaertner appeared for the State.  Defendant in custody and appeared in court w/ Attorney Bub.  Clerk. M.Burke. Dr. Niess appears by zoom. DE states he is competent. Atty Gaertner states she believes the DE is not competent. Dr. Niess sworn in and testifies. Court finds DE incompetent for reasons set forth on the record. Court orders DE commited to inpatient psychiatric treatment. Court believes the DE is likely to regain competency. Case suspended.

Attorney Emily Gaertner appeared for the State. Defendant in custody by zoom w/ Attorney C Bub. Clerk/H. Barnett. Deft states he believes he is neither competent nor incompetent. Contested competency hearing set for 5/9/22 at 3:30pm. Bond continued.
With Atty Bub the CH of 3/16/22 at 8:30am is rescheduled, as Judge Rossell granted an extension for Dr. Niess to complete the exam and report; reset to 3/28/22 at 2pm.
Vicki/WI Forensic Unit was notified that Judge Rossell is granting Dr. Niess' request for an extension to complete the competency exam and report until 3/23/22.
